  keywords={Humanism, Humanities, Surgical Instruments, Stress, Mechanical, Spine, Spinal Fusion, Spinal Fractures, Sex Factors, Reproducibility of Results, Range of Motion, Articular, Prospective Studies, Predictive Value of Tests, Middle Aged, Male, Magnetic Resonance Imaging, Lumbosacral Region, Intraoperative Period, Intervertebral Disc Displacement, Humans, Female, Elasticity, Diagnostic Equipment, Decompression, Surgical, Biomechanical Phenomena, Aged, 80 and over, Aged, Age Factors, Adult, Adolescent},
  abstract={Study design: 
Prospective trial.
Objectives: 
To test an intraoperative diagnostic tool to determine if it provided the surgeon with a safe, reproducible, accurate, quantitative measure of lumbar spine motion segment stability.
Summary of background data: 
