  abstract={Study design: 
Biomechanical cadaveric bench study.
Objective: 
To measure motion at the fracture site in an osteoporotic cadaveric sacral insufficiency fracture model before and after fracture creation, after fixation (via 1 of 3 fixation techniques), and after cyclic loading and to compare those values with motion of the intact pelvis.
Summary of background data: 
