  abstract={Objective: 
To determine the effectiveness and safety of percutaneous vertebroplasty for the treatment of osteoporotic vertebral compression fractures as published in the scientific literature.
Design: 
Literature review.
Method: 
Medline and the Cochrane library were searched with the terms 'percutaneous vertebroplasty', 'vertebral compression fractures', 'osteoporotic' and 'osteoporosis'. Criteria for inclusion were: (a) the studies had to have been published in the period January 1985-August 2002, (b) the study population had to include at least 10 patients, (c) the patients had to have been treated with percutaneous vertebroplasty, and (d) the diagnosis had to have been 'osteoporotic vertebral compression fracture'.
Results: 
